# Fix UI Crash on Navigation

The user reports a black screen crash when navigating sidebar sections. This is likely caused by the [AdminProducts](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx#167-218) component trying to filter an undefined `products` prop before the data fetch completes or if it fails.

## Root Cause
`const filtered = filterType ? products.filter((p: any) => p.type === filterType) : products;`

If `products` is `undefined` (initial state or fetch error), this line throws a runtime error, causing the React component tree to crash.

## Proposed Changes

### [MODIFY] [src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx)
- Add a safety check for `products` in [AdminProducts](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx#167-218).
- Return an empty array or null if `products` is missing.
- Add similar safety checks for [KeyManagementView](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx#219-265) and [AdminOrders](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx#266-307).

```typescript
